29 holiday, then the salary payment shall be made on the next
30 succeeding workday.
31 (c) A local board of education may opt out of the
32 provisions of this section by written board resolution. The
33 board must file this resolution with the State Superintendent
34 of Education within 60 days of passage of the resolution.
35 (d) The Comptroller, the State Superintendent of
36 Education, and the State Board of Education shall adopt
37 policies to implement the provisions of this section.
38 (e) It is the intent of the Legislature that the
39 implementation of a semi-monthly pay plan shall not reduce any
40 employee's annual rate of compensation.
41 Section 2. This act shall become effective on July 1,
42 2026.
